After righting Go for over 2 years now, and currently doing it full time as a job, I have a huge appreciation for the authors doing this
I've always had a feeling that they were on to something and that if something I was trying to do was difficult, that it was just Wrong
The authors made it simple and small so that you would be forced into the right way of doing things.
I know that people think of Go as a simple, small language, but I think the learning curve is actually deceptively steep after a while
